-- Vietnam Stocks: Kinh Bac City, Thu Duc Housing, SMC Investment
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-04-12T08:14:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/vietnam-stocks-kinh-bac-city-thu-duc-housing-smc-investment.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 2:15 p.m. local-time close
in Ho Chi Minh City. The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the
Ho Chi Minh City Stock Exchange, rose for a sixth day, adding
1.4 percent to 465.26, the highest since Sept. 15.  Property Stocks:  Kinh Bac City Development Share Holding
Corp. (KBC)  , Vietnam’s third-biggest property firm by market
value, gained 3.9 percent to 15,800 dong, the highest close
since March 9.  Thu Duc Housing Development Joint-Stock Co. (TDH)  , a real-estate firm backed by Deutsche Bank AG, surged 4.9
percent to 17,100 dong, the highest in more than six months.  Dat
Xanh Real Estate Service & Construction Joint-Stock Co. (DXG)  
jumped by the daily limit of 5 percent to 10,500 dong, the
highest close since Dec. 1.  The central bank eased lending regulations yesterday to
give homebuyers better access to loans. “Banks now can give out
more loans for home purchases,” Nguyen Hoai Nam, deputy head of
research at Kim Eng Vietnam Securities Co., said by phone from
Hanoi. “Property companies will benefit as they will be able to
reduce their inventory.”  SMC Investment Trading Joint-Stock Co. (SMC)  , a steel
trader in Ho Chi Minh City, surged 4.7 percent to 11,100 dong,
the highest close since Nov. 1. Chairman and General Director
Nguyen Ngoc Anh rose his stake in the company to 15.6 percent
from 14.3 percent, according to an exchange filing.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
